<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Seeds of <i>Arctostaphylos crustacea </i>and <i>A. tomentosa </i>germinate after a fire. Seedling mortality is high during the first year of growth. Top-killed plants sprout from the lignotuber. Shrubs gain dominance within 10-15 years and create a closed shrub canopy that adds to the seed bank. Stands require periodic fire to maintain current species composition. Greenlee and Langenheim (1990) and Van Dyke et al. (2001) considered historic fire cycle to be between 10 and 100 years for some maritime chaparral types, though an interval of > 50 years is likely to maintain the alliance.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (30-100+ years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
